1. Initialize variables for left index, maxLeft index, and result string.
2. Use a while loop to iterate through the string.
3. Inside the loop, check if the current character is consecutive with the next character. If so, add the current character to the result string and increment the left index.
4. If the current index is greater than the maxLeft index, update maxLeft to the current index.
5. Continue iterating until all characters have been checked.
6. Return the result string after the loop ends.
7. Define a helper method to check if two characters are consecutive.
8. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the string once.
9. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the result string and helper method.
